NAME - ::<namespace>:: emulation_stp_bridge_config

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

This command is used to create/modify/delete/enable/disable a STP bridge. Each STP bridge can have multiple STP router interfaces. Each bridge interface is associated with a protocol interface.By specifying the intf_... parameters there will be created a number of interfaces equal to intf_count of directly connected interfaces per STP bridge.

SYNOPSIS - ::<namespace>::emulation_stp_bridge_config

List arguments in the alphabetical order or in the reverse alphabetical order.

ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

-auto_pick_bridge_mac

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

If enabled, the MAC address for one of the STP interfaces will be automatically assigned as the MAC address for this Bridge. If disabled, the user can assign a MAC address for this Bridge.This option is valid only when -mode is create or -mode is modify and -handle is provided.Valid options are: 0 - disabled, 1 - enabled.

DEFAULT

1

-auto_pick_port

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

If enabled, each STP interface configured for the same bridge will be assigned a unique port number automatically. Additional port numbers for interfaces on the same bridge will be incremented by 1. This option is valid only when -mode is create or -mode modify and -handle is provided as a STP bridge interface handle or as an STP bridge handle (both handles are returned by emulation_stp_bridge_config). If the change is to be applied on an STP bridge handle it will be applied for all its interfaces.Valid options are: 0 - disabled, 1 - enabled.

DEFAULT

1

-bridge_mac

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The 6-byte MAC Address of this emulated Bridge. Part of the Bridge Identifier (Bridge ID). This option is valid only when -mode is create or -mode is modify and -handle is provided.

DEFAULT

0F00.0000.0000

-bridge_mac_step

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The 6-byte MAC Address of this emulated Bridge. Part of the Bridge Identifier (Bridge ID). This option is valid only when -mode is create or -mode is modify and -handle is provided.

DEFAULT

0000.0000.0001

-bridge_mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The type of spanning tree protocol to be used for this emulated Bridge. All of the emulated bridges on a port should use the same version of the spanning tree protocol - STP, RSTP, MSTP, PVST+, RPVST+ or PVSTP. The DUT should also use the same version of the protocol.

Valid options are:

stp

Spanning Tree Protocol

rstp

Rapid Spanning Tree Protocol (the default)

mstp

Multiple Spanning Tree Protocol

pvst

Per-VLAN Spanning Tree Plus Protocol

rpvst

Rapid Per-VLAN Spanning Tree Plus Protocol

pvstp

Per-VLAN Spanning Tree

DEFAULT

rstp

-bridge_msti_vlan

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

This parameter is valid only for bridge_mode mstp, pvst and rpvst. The parameter specifies the MSTI/VLAN to be used by the bridge. Valid options are:allnoneThis option is valid only when -mode is modify and -handle is provided as a STP bridge interface handle or as an STP bridge handle (both handles are returned by emulation_stp_bridge_config). If the change is to be applied on an STP bridge handle it will be applied for all its interfaces.

DEFAULT

 None

-bridge_priority

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The unsigned integer value assigned as the Priority for the Root Bridge. Part of the Root Bridge Identifier (Root Bridge ID). Since MAC address reduction is used, only multiples of 4096 are used. Choose one of the following values from the list: 0 4096 8192 12288 16384 20480 24576 28672 32768 36864 40960 45056 49152 53248 57344 61440. This option is valid only when -mode is create or -mode is modify and -handle is provided.

DEFAULT

32768

-bridge_system_id

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The unsigned integer value assigned as the System ID for this Bridge. Part of the Bridge Identifier (Bridge ID).This option is valid only when: -mode is create and -bridge_mode is stp/rstp, or -mode is modify and -handle is provided.

DEFAULT

0

-cist_external_root_cost

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Common and Internal Spanning Tree (CIST) regional (external) root path cost. A 4-byte unsigned integer. This option is valid only when: -mode is create and -bridge_mode is mstp, or -mode is modify and -handle is provided.

DEFAULT

0

-cist_reg_root_priority

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Since MAC address reduction is used, only multiples of 4096 are used. For MSTP is the priority value of the root bridge for the Common and internal Spanning Tree (CIST)/MSTP region (external). Part of the CIST External Root Identifier. Since MAC address reduction is used, only multiples of 4096 are used. Choose one of the following values from the list 0 4096 8192 12288 16384 20480 24576 28672 32768 36864 40960 45056 49152 53248 57344 61440. This option is valid only when: -mode is create and -bridge_mode is mstp, or -mode is modify and -handle is provided.

DEFAULT

32768

-cist_remaining_hop

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The number of additional bridge-to-bridge hops that will allowed for the MSTP BPDUs. The root sets the maximum hop count, and each subsequent bridge decrements this value by 1. This option is valid only when: -mode is create and -bridge_mode is mstp, or -mode is modify and -handle is provided.

DEFAULT

20

-count

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

This parameter represents the number of emulated bridges to create. A number between 1 and 200 must be provided. This option is valid only in mode create.

DEFAULT

1

0000.0000.0000

-cst_root_path_cost

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

A 4-byte unsigned integer is administrative path cost to the root bridge. This option is valid only when: -mode is create and -bridge_mode is pvst/rpvst, or -mode is modify and -handle is provided.

DEFAULT

0

-cst_root_priority

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Is the priority value of the root bridge for the Common Spanning Tree (CST). Since MAC address reduction is used, only multiples of 4096 are used. Choose one of the following values from the list 0 4096 8192 12288 16384 20480 24576 28672 32768 36864 40960 45056 49152 53248 57344 61440. This option is valid only when: -mode is create and -bridge_mode is pvst/rpvst, or -mode is modify and -handle is provided.

DEFAULT

32768

-cst_vlan_port_priority

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The Port Priority for the emulated port on this PVST+ or RPVST+ bridge that is connected to the VLAN. A 2-byte unsigned integer. The valid range is 0 to 63. This option is valid only when: -mode is create and -bridge_mode is pvst/rpvst, or -mode is modify and -handle is provided.

DEFAULT

32

-enable_jitter

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

If checked, jitter is enabled in order to stagger the transmission of Hello BPDUs and avoid congestion on the link. This option is valid only when -mode is create or -mode modify and -handle is provided as a STP bridge interface handle or as an STP bridge handle (both handles are returned by emulation_stp_bridge_config). If the change is to be applied on an STP bridge handle it will be applied for all its interfaces.

DEFAULT

0

-forward_delay

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The Forward Delay Timer. The delay time used for a port's change to the Forwarding state. This value is set by the Root Bridge. This option is valid only when -mode is create or -mode is modify and -handle is provided.

DEFAULT

15000

-handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

This option represents a STP bridge handle for modify, enable, disable or delete.This option is valid when -mode is modify, delete, enable or disable.

DEFAULT

 None

-hello_interval

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The period of time between transmissions of Hello Messages from the Root Bridge. This option is valid only when -mode is create or -mode is modify and -handle is provided.

DEFAULT

2000

-inter_bdpu_gap

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The interval between transmissions of BPDUs (in msec). The valid range is 0 to 60,000 msec.This option is valid only when -mode is create or -mode modify and -handle is provided.

DEFAULT

0

-override_existence_check

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

If this option is enabled, the interface existence check is skipped but the list of interfaces is still created and maintained in order to keep track of existing interfaces if required. Using this option will speed up the creation of the interfaces.

DEFAULT

0

-override_tracking

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

If this option is enabled, the list of interfaces will no longer be created and maintained, thus speeding up the creation of interfaces even more. Also, it will enable -override_existence_check in case it was not already enabled because checking for interface existence becomes impossible if the list of interfaces does not exist anymore.

DEFAULT

0

NAME - <namespace>::emulation_stp_bridge_config

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

This command is used to create/modify/delete/enable/disable a STP bridge. Each STP bridge can have multiple STP router interfaces. Each bridge interface is associated with a protocol interface.By specifying the intf_... parameters there will be created a number of interfaces equal to intf_count of directly connected interfaces per STP bridge.

bridge_mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The type of spanning tree protocol to be used for this emulated Bridge. All of the emulated bridges on a port should use the same version of the spanning tree protocol - STP, RSTP, MSTP, PVST+, RPVST+ or PVSTP. The DUT should also use the same version of the protocol.

Valid options are:

stp

Spanning Tree Protocol

rstp

Rapid Spanning Tree Protocol (the default)

mstp

Multiple Spanning Tree Protocol

pvst

Per-VLAN Spanning Tree Plus Protocol

rpvst

Rapid Per-VLAN Spanning Tree Plus Protocol

pvstp

Per-VLAN Spanning Tree

DEFAULT

rstp

NAME - <namespace>::emulation_stp_bridge_config

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

This command is used to create/modify/delete/enable/disable a STP bridge. Each STP bridge can have multiple STP router interfaces. Each bridge interface is associated with a protocol interface.By specifying the intf_... parameters there will be created a number of interfaces equal to intf_count of directly connected interfaces per STP bridge.

SYNOPSIS - ::<namespace>::emulation_stp_bridge_config

bridge_mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The type of spanning tree protocol to be used for this emulated Bridge. All of the emulated bridges on a port should use the same version of the spanning tree protocol - STP, RSTP, MSTP, PVST+, RPVST+ or PVSTP. The DUT should also use the same version of the protocol.

Valid options are:

stp

Spanning Tree Protocol

rstp

Rapid Spanning Tree Protocol (the default)

mstp

Multiple Spanning Tree Protocol

pvst

Per-VLAN Spanning Tree Plus Protocol

rpvst

Rapid Per-VLAN Spanning Tree Plus Protocol

pvstp

Per-VLAN Spanning Tree

DEFAULT

rstp
